<p>A problem by Soviet physicist Viktor Lange:</p>
<p>&#8220;By lifting up a bucket of coal to a third floor stove we increase the potential energy of the coal by about 800 J (the force of gravity on the coal is about 80 N and it is raised by about 10 m). Where will this additional potential energy go to when this coal is burnt in the stove?&#8221;</p>

<div class='easySpoilerWrapper' style=''>
